text: USS Ticonderoga may refer to: * was a 17-gun schooner in service from 1814 to 1825 * was a screw sloop-of-war in commission from 1863 to 1881 * was a former German cargo ship that served the Naval Overseas Transportation Service during World War I in 1917 and 1918 * was a long-hull fleet aircraft carrier which served from 1944 to 1973 * was a guided missile cruiser and lead ship of her class. Launched in 1981, she was decommissioned on 30 September 2004 Category:United States Navy ship names
title: USS Ticonderoga
